.TH WARRENVPND 8 "2026" "WarrenVPN" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
warrenvpnd \- WarrenVPN VPN privileged daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B /usr/lib/warrenvpn/warrenvpnd
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B warrenvpnd
is the privileged D\-Bus system service (\fInet.warrenvpn.WarrenVPN1\fR) behind the
WarrenVPN VPN GUI and \fBwarrenvpnctl\fR(1). It is the product's only security boundary:
it authorizes every privileged operation with polkit, re\-parses and re\-classifies
configurations server\-side, stores root\-owned shadow copies, launches and drives
OpenVPN via its management interface, configures DNS through systemd\-resolved, and
manages the nftables kill\-switch.
.PP
It is D\-Bus\-activated; there is normally no need to start it manually.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B WARRENVPND_BUS=session
Use the session bus (development).
.TP
.B WARRENVPND_STATE_DIR, WARRENVPND_RUNTIME_DIR, WARRENVPND_OPENVPN_PATH, WARRENVPND_UPDOWN_PATH
Relocate state / select the openvpn and up\-down helper (development/packaging).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/warrenvpn/users/<uid>/
Root\-owned shadow configurations (the only copy OpenVPN is launched against).
.TP
.I /etc/warrenvpn/
Forced (administrator) preferences and shared configurations.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR warrenvpn (1),
.BR warrenvpnctl (1),
.BR polkit (8),
.BR nft (8),
.BR resolvectl (1)
